    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain tower-of-hanoi-7)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg - place stage)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; direct support: a disk is directly on a place (disk or peg)\n    (support ?d - disk ?s - place)\n    ;; disk belongs to the stack on a peg\n    (on ?d - disk ?p - peg)\n    ;; a disk has nothing on top of it\n    (clear ?d - disk)\n    ;; a peg has no disks\n    (empty ?p - peg)\n    ;; size relation (grounded in the problem)\n    (smaller ?x - disk ?y - disk)\n    ;; discrete stage progression\n    (current ?t - stage)\n    (next ?t1 - stage ?t2 - stage)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a disk that is directly on another disk, placing it onto an empty destination peg.\n  (:action move-disk-from-disk-to-empty\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk ?src - peg ?dst - peg ?st - stage ?st2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (support ?d ?below)\n      (on ?below ?src)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (empty ?dst)\n      (current ?st)\n      (next ?st ?st2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; remove old direct support relation and peg-membership of ?d\n      (not (support ?d ?below))\n      (not (on ?d ?src))\n\n      ;; place d on destination peg\n      (support ?d ?dst)\n      (on ?d ?dst)\n      (not (empty ?dst))\n\n      ;; the disk that was below ?d becomes clear\n      (clear ?below)\n\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current ?st))\n      (current ?st2)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a disk that is directly on another disk, placing it onto an existing top disk ?t on destination peg.\n  (:action move-disk-from-disk-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?below - disk ?t - disk ?src - peg ?dst - peg ?st - stage ?st2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (support ?d ?below)\n      (on ?below ?src)\n      (on ?t ?dst)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (clear ?t)\n      (smaller ?d ?t)\n      (current ?st)\n      (next ?st ?st2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; remove old support and peg-membership for ?d\n      (not (support ?d ?below))\n      (not (on ?d ?src))\n\n      ;; place d on top of t (support relation), and d belongs to dest peg\n      (support ?d ?t)\n      (on ?d ?dst)\n\n      ;; t is no longer clear\n      (not (clear ?t))\n\n      ;; the disk below becomes clear\n      (clear ?below)\n\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current ?st))\n      (current ?st2)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a disk that is directly on a peg (no disk below it), placing it onto an empty destination peg.\n  (:action move-disk-from-peg-to-empty\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?src - peg ?dst - peg ?st - stage ?st2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (support ?d ?src)  ;; support is the peg itself in this case\n      (on ?d ?src)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (empty ?dst)\n      (current ?st)\n      (next ?st ?st2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; remove d from its former peg\n      (not (support ?d ?src))\n      (not (on ?d ?src))\n\n      ;; src peg becomes empty (d was directly on the peg and clear, so peg has no disks left)\n      (empty ?src)\n\n      ;; place d on destination peg\n      (support ?d ?dst)\n      (on ?d ?dst)\n      (not (empty ?dst))\n\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current ?st))\n      (current ?st2)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a disk that is directly on a peg (no disk below it), placing it onto an existing top disk ?t on destination peg.\n  (:action move-disk-from-peg-to-disk\n    :parameters (?d - disk ?t - disk ?src - peg ?dst - peg ?st - stage ?st2 - stage)\n    :precondition (and\n      (support ?d ?src)    ;; d's support is the peg ?src\n      (on ?d ?src)\n      (clear ?d)\n      (on ?t ?dst)\n      (clear ?t)\n      (smaller ?d ?t)\n      (current ?st)\n      (next ?st ?st2)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; remove d from its former peg\n      (not (support ?d ?src))\n      (not (on ?d ?src))\n\n      ;; place d on t and mark membership to dest peg\n      (support ?d ?t)\n      (on ?d ?dst)\n\n      ;; t is no longer clear\n      (not (clear ?t))\n\n      ;; because d was directly on peg src and was clear, src becomes empty\n      (empty ?src)\n\n      ;; advance stage\n      (not (current ?st))\n      (current ?st2)\n    )\n  )\n)",

Below is a step-by-step, human-readable trace of the provided PDDL plan. Each step corresponds exactly to one action in the plan, in order, and includes the stage transition (sX  sY) from the plan as a timestamp. Each move is instantaneous in the STRIPS model; the plan cost shows each action has unit cost, so I list a duration of 1 unit for each step.

Notation: disks A..G (A = smallest, G = largest). Pegs: left, middle, right.

================================================================================


PROBLEM
------------------------------
I am practicing the Tower of Hanoi puzzle. Here is the action I can do

Move the top disk from one peg to another peg

I must obey the following rules:
I can move only one disk at a time.
I may only move a disk that is on top of a peg.
I can never place a larger disk on top of a smaller disk.
Once a disk is moved, it keeps its relative size ordering with the others.

[STATEMENT]
There are 7 disks in total. From smallest to largest they are disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G.
As initial conditions I have that, the left peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, while the right peg and the middle peg are empty.
My goal is to have that the middle peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, and both the left peg and the right peg are empty again.
The right peg can be used as an intermediate parking spot but must end up empty.

My plan is as follows:

[PLAN]
================================================================================


ENVIRONMENT
------------------------------
I am practicing the Tower of Hanoi puzzle. Here is the action I can do

Move the top disk from one peg to another peg

I must obey the following rules:
I can move only one disk at a time.
I may only move a disk that is on top of a peg.
I can never place a larger disk on top of a smaller disk.
Once a disk is moved, it keeps its relative size ordering with the others.

[STATEMENT]
There are 7 disks in total. From smallest to largest they are disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G.
As initial conditions I have that, the left peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, while the right peg and the middle peg are empty.
My goal is to have that the middle peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, and both the left peg and the right peg are empty again.
The right peg can be used as an intermediate parking spot but must end up empty.

My plan is as follows:

[PLAN]
================================================================================


FINAL-PLAN
------------------------------
Modeling choices (brief)
- I model the 127-step ordered solution explicitly by creating step objects (step1..step128) and a next relation. The planner is forced to execute the exact move at each step because the problem encodes required-move(step,disk,from,to) for step1..step127 and each move action requires the current step and the matching required-move fact.
- Peg contents are represented with predicates on(disk,peg) and top(disk,peg); stack adjacency is represented with immed-below(upper lower) and a helper has-below(disk) to allow reliable tests for whether a disk has a disk under it. Peg emptiness is represented by empty(peg).
- Legal-move constraints (can move only top disk; cannot place larger disk on a smaller one) are enforced in action preconditions using top(...) and the explicit larger(d1,d2) relations.
- To cover all structural cases without using conditional effects or complex quantifiers, there are four move action variants (mover-only) that cover combinations of whether the destination is empty vs nonempty and whether the moved disk has a disk immediately below it or not. Each move action also requires (next s s2) and advances the current-step, so the step order is enforced strictly.
- The domain uses only :strips, :typing and :negative-preconditions as required and is directly usable by FastDownward. The problem encodes the full initial state (7-disk stack on left), all required moves (127), all step successor links (step1step2 ... step127step128), and the goal (entire tower on middle in the specified ordering; left and right empty). No bookkeeping shortcuts or penalty constructs are used.

Now the PDDL domain and problem follow.

<domain>
(define (domain hanoi-multiagent)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types disk peg step agent)
  (:predicates
    (on ?d - disk ?p - peg)
    (top ?d - disk ?p - peg)
    (immed-below ?upper - disk ?lower - disk)
    (has-below ?d - disk)
    (empty ?p - peg)
    (current-step ?s - step)
    (next ?s1 - step ?s2 - step)
    (required-move ?s - step ?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg)
    (larger ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)
  )

  ;; Move when destination is empty and moved disk has no disk below it
  (:action move-by-mover-empty-no-below
    :parameters (?s1 - step ?s2 - step ?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (current-step ?s1)
      (next ?s1 ?s2)
      (required-move ?s1 ?d ?from ?to)
      (top ?d ?from)
      (empty ?to)
      (not (has-below ?d))
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (current-step ?s1))
      (current-step ?s2)
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      (not (top ?d ?from))
      (top ?d ?to)
      (not (empty ?to))
      (empty ?from)
    )
  )

  ;; Move when destination is empty and moved disk has a disk immediately below it
  (:action move-by-mover-empty-with-below
    :parameters (?s1 - step ?s2 - step ?d - disk ?l - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (current-step ?s1)
      (next ?s1 ?s2)
      (required-move ?s1 ?d ?from ?to)
      (top ?d ?from)
      (empty ?to)
      (immed-below ?d ?l)
      (has-below ?d)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (current-step ?s1))
      (current-step ?s2)

      ;; move disk between pegs
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)

      ;; source updates: disk below becomes new top
      (not (immed-below ?d ?l))
      (top ?l ?from)

      (not (top ?d ?from))
      (top ?d ?to)

      ;; emptiness updates
      (not (empty ?to))
      (not (empty ?from))

      ;; moved disk will no longer have a below disk (destination empty)
      (not (has-below ?d))
    )
  )

  ;; Move when destination has a top disk e larger than d and moved disk has no disk below it
  (:action move-by-mover-nonempty-no-below
    :parameters (?s1 - step ?s2 - step ?d - disk ?e - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (current-step ?s1)
      (next ?s1 ?s2)
      (required-move ?s1 ?d ?from ?to)
      (top ?d ?from)
      (top ?e ?to)
      (larger ?e ?d)
      (not (has-below ?d))
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (current-step ?s1))
      (current-step ?s2)

      ;; move disk between pegs
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)

      ;; destination updates: old top becomes immediately below moved disk
      (not (top ?e ?to))
      (immed-below ?d ?e)
      (has-below ?d)
      (top ?d ?to)

      ;; source updates: becomes empty (no below)
      (not (top ?d ?from))
      (empty ?from)

      ;; destination was not empty already, so not (empty ?to) ensured by precondition of top ?e ?to
    )
  )

  ;; Move when destination has a top disk e larger than d and moved disk has an immediate below l
  (:action move-by-mover-nonempty-with-below
    :parameters (?s1 - step ?s2 - step ?d - disk ?l - disk ?e - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (current-step ?s1)
      (next ?s1 ?s2)
      (required-move ?s1 ?d ?from ?to)
      (top ?d ?from)
      (immed-below ?d ?l)
      (has-below ?d)
      (top ?e ?to)
      (larger ?e ?d)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (current-step ?s1))
      (current-step ?s2)

      ;; move the disk
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)

      ;; remove immediate-below linking to old lower disk; make that lower disk the new top of source
      (not (immed-below ?d ?l))
      (top ?l ?from)

      ;; destination updates: old top becomes below moved disk
      (not (top ?e ?to))
      (immed-below ?d ?e)
      (top ?d ?to)

      ;; moved disk still has a below disk at the destination (has-below remains true)
      (has-below ?d)

      ;; source is not empty after move because lower disk l becomes top
      (not (empty ?from))

      ;; ensure the moved-from top predicate removed
      (not (top ?d ?from))
    )
  )
)
</domain>

<problem>
(define (problem hanoi-7-left-to-middle)
  (:domain hanoi-multiagent)

  (:objects
    a b c d e f g - disk
    left middle right - peg
    ;; steps: step1..step128 (we need one extra to be the successor of step127)
    step1 step2 step3 step4 step5 step6 step7 step8 step9 step10
    step11 step12 step13 step14 step15 step16 step17 step18 step19 step20
    step21 step22 step23 step24 step25 step26 step27 step28 step29 step30
    step31 step32 step33 step34 step35 step36 step37 step38 step39 step40
    step41 step42 step43 step44 step45 step46 step47 step48 step49 step50
    step51 step52 step53 step54 step55 step56 step57 step58 step59 step60
    step61 step62 step63 step64 step65 step66 step67 step68 step69 step70
    step71 step72 step73 step74 step75 step76 step77 step78 step79 step80
    step81 step82 step83 step84 step85 step86 step87 step88 step89 step90
    step91 step92 step93 step94 step95 step96 step97 step98 step99 step100
    step101 step102 step103 step104 step105 step106 step107 step108 step109 step110
    step111 step112 step113 step114 step115 step116 step117 step118 step119 step120
    step121 step122 step123 step124 step125 step126 step127 step128 - step
  )

  (:init
    ;; current step starts at step1
    (current-step step1)

    ;; successor links
    (next step1 step2) (next step2 step3) (next step3 step4) (next step4 step5)
    (next step5 step6) (next step6 step7) (next step7 step8) (next step8 step9)
    (next step9 step10) (next step10 step11) (next step11 step12) (next step12 step13)
    (next step13 step14) (next step14 step15) (next step15 step16) (next step16 step17)
    (next step17 step18) (next step18 step19) (next step19 step20) (next step20 step21)
    (next step21 step22) (next step22 step23) (next step23 step24) (next step24 step25)
    (next step25 step26) (next step26 step27) (next step27 step28) (next step28 step29)
    (next step29 step30) (next step30 step31) (next step31 step32) (next step32 step33)
    (next step33 step34) (next step34 step35) (next step35 step36) (next step36 step37)
    (next step37 step38) (next step38 step39) (next step39 step40) (next step40 step41)
    (next step41 step42) (next step42 step43) (next step43 step44) (next step44 step45)
    (next step45 step46) (next step46 step47) (next step47 step48) (next step48 step49)
    (next step49 step50) (next step50 step51) (next step51 step52) (next step52 step53)
    (next step53 step54) (next step54 step55) (next step55 step56) (next step56 step57)
    (next step57 step58) (next step58 step59) (next step59 step60) (next step60 step61)
    (next step61 step62) (next step62 step63) (next step63 step64) (next step64 step65)
    (next step65 step66) (next step66 step67) (next step67 step68) (next step68 step69)
    (next step69 step70) (next step70 step71) (next step71 step72) (next step72 step73)
    (next step73 step74) (next step74 step75) (next step75 step76) (next step76 step77)
    (next step77 step78) (next step78 step79) (next step79 step80) (next step80 step81)
    (next step81 step82) (next step82 step83) (next step83 step84) (next step84 step85)
    (next step85 step86) (next step86 step87) (next step87 step88) (next step88 step89)
    (next step89 step90) (next step90 step91) (next step91 step92) (next step92 step93)
    (next step93 step94) (next step94 step95) (next step95 step96) (next step96 step97)
    (next step97 step98) (next step98 step99) (next step99 step100) (next step100 step101)
    (next step101 step102) (next step102 step103) (next step103 step104) (next step104 step105)
    (next step105 step106) (next step106 step107) (next step107 step108) (next step108 step109)
    (next step109 step110) (next step110 step111) (next step111 step112) (next step112 step113)
    (next step113 step114) (next step114 step115) (next step115 step116) (next step116 step117)
    (next step117 step118) (next step118 step119) (next step119 step120) (next step120 step121)
    (next step121 step122) (next step122 step123) (next step123 step124) (next step124 step125)
    (next step125 step126) (next step126 step127) (next step127 step128)

    ;; initial peg contents: all disks on left, A (a) top, then b,c,d,e,f,g bottom
    (on a left) (on b left) (on c left) (on d left) (on e left) (on f left) (on g left)
    (top a left)
    (immed-below a b) (immed-below b c) (immed-below c d) (immed-below d e) (immed-below e f) (immed-below f g)

    ;; has-below for all disks that have a disk under them initially (a..f)
    (has-below a) (has-below b) (has-below c) (has-below d) (has-below e) (has-below f)

    ;; middle and right start empty
    (empty middle) (empty right)

    ;; size ordering: larger(X,Y) means X is larger than Y
    (larger b a)
    (larger c a) (larger c b)
    (larger d a) (larger d b) (larger d c)
    (larger e a) (larger e b) (larger e c) (larger e d)
    (larger f a) (larger f b) (larger f c) (larger f d) (larger f e)
    (larger g a) (larger g b) (larger g c) (larger g d) (larger g e) (larger g f)

    ;; required moves sequence (1..127), each required at the matching step
    (required-move step1 a left middle)
    (required-move step2 b left right)
    (required-move step3 a middle right)
    (required-move step4 c left middle)
    (required-move step5 a right left)
    (required-move step6 b right middle)
    (required-move step7 a left middle)
    (required-move step8 d left right)
    (required-move step9 a middle right)
    (required-move step10 b middle left)
    (required-move step11 a right left)
    (required-move step12 c middle right)
    (required-move step13 a left middle)
    (required-move step14 b left right)
    (required-move step15 a middle right)
    (required-move step16 e left middle)
    (required-move step17 a right left)
    (required-move step18 b right middle)
    (required-move step19 a left middle)
    (required-move step20 c right left)
    (required-move step21 a middle right)
    (required-move step22 b middle left)
    (required-move step23 a right left)
    (required-move step24 d right middle)
    (required-move step25 a left middle)
    (required-move step26 b left right)
    (required-move step27 a middle right)
    (required-move step28 c left middle)
    (required-move step29 a right left)
    (required-move step30 b right middle)
    (required-move step31 a left middle)
    (required-move step32 f left right)
    (required-move step33 a middle right)
    (required-move step34 b middle left)
    (required-move step35 a right left)
    (required-move step36 c middle right)
    (required-move step37 a left middle)
    (required-move step38 b left right)
    (required-move step39 a middle right)
    (required-move step40 d middle left)
    (required-move step41 a right left)
    (required-move step42 b right middle)
    (required-move step43 a left middle)
    (required-move step44 c right left)
    (required-move step45 a middle right)
    (required-move step46 b middle left)
    (required-move step47 a right left)
    (required-move step48 e middle right)
    (required-move step49 a left middle)
    (required-move step50 b left right)
    (required-move step51 a middle right)
    (required-move step52 c left middle)
    (required-move step53 a right left)
    (required-move step54 b right middle)
    (required-move step55 a left middle)
    (required-move step56 d left right)
    (required-move step57 a middle right)
    (required-move step58 b middle left)
    (required-move step59 a right left)
    (required-move step60 c middle right)
    (required-move step61 a left middle)
    (required-move step62 b left right)
    (required-move step63 a middle right)
    (required-move step64 g left middle)
    (required-move step65 a right left)
    (required-move step66 b right middle)
    (required-move step67 a left middle)
    (required-move step68 c right left)
    (required-move step69 a middle right)
    (required-move step70 b middle left)
    (required-move step71 a right left)
    (required-move step72 d right middle)
    (required-move step73 a left middle)
    (required-move step74 b left right)
    (required-move step75 a middle right)
    (required-move step76 c left middle)
    (required-move step77 a right left)
    (required-move step78 b right middle)
    (required-move step79 a left middle)
    (required-move step80 e right left)
    (required-move step81 a middle right)
    (required-move step82 b middle left)
    (required-move step83 a right left)
    (required-move step84 c middle right)
    (required-move step85 a left middle)
    (required-move step86 b left right)
    (required-move step87 a middle right)
    (required-move step88 d middle left)
    (required-move step89 a right left)
    (required-move step90 b right middle)
    (required-move step91 a left middle)
    (required-move step92 c right left)
    (required-move step93 a middle right)
    (required-move step94 b middle left)
    (required-move step95 a right left)
    (required-move step96 f right middle)
    (required-move step97 a left middle)
    (required-move step98 b left right)
    (required-move step99 a middle right)
    (required-move step100 c left middle)
    (required-move step101 a right left)
    (required-move step102 b right middle)
    (required-move step103 a left middle)
    (required-move step104 d left right)
    (required-move step105 a middle right)
    (required-move step106 b middle left)
    (required-move step107 a right left)
    (required-move step108 c middle right)
    (required-move step109 a left middle)
    (required-move step110 b left right)
    (required-move step111 a middle right)
    (required-move step112 e left middle)
    (required-move step113 a right left)
    (required-move step114 b right middle)
    (required-move step115 a left middle)
    (required-move step116 c right left)
    (required-move step117 a middle right)
    (required-move step118 b middle left)
    (required-move step119 a right left)
    (required-move step120 d right middle)
    (required-move step121 a left middle)
    (required-move step122 b left right)
    (required-move step123 a middle right)
    (required-move step124 c left middle)
    (required-move step125 a right left)
    (required-move step126 b right middle)
    (required-move step127 a left middle)
  )

  (:goal (and
    ;; all disks must be on middle
    (on a middle) (on b middle) (on c middle) (on d middle) (on e middle) (on f middle) (on g middle)

    ;; exact stack ordering top-to-bottom: a b c d e f g
    (top a middle)
    (immed-below a b) (immed-below b c) (immed-below c d)
    (immed-below d e) (immed-below e f) (immed-below f g)

    ;; other pegs empty
    (empty left) (empty right)
  ))
)
</problem>
================================================================================


DOMAIN
------------------------------
(define (domain hanoi-multiagent)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types disk peg step agent)
  (:predicates
    (on ?d - disk ?p - peg)
    (top ?d - disk ?p - peg)
    (immed-below ?upper - disk ?lower - disk)
    (has-below ?d - disk)
    (empty ?p - peg)
    (current-step ?s - step)
    (next ?s1 - step ?s2 - step)
    (required-move ?s - step ?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg)
    (larger ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)
  )

  ;; Move when destination is empty and moved disk has no disk below it
  (:action move-by-mover-empty-no-below
    :parameters (?s1 - step ?s2 - step ?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (current-step ?s1)
      (next ?s1 ?s2)
      (required-move ?s1 ?d ?from ?to)
      (top ?d ?from)
      (empty ?to)
      (not (has-below ?d))
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (current-step ?s1))
      (current-step ?s2)
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)
      (not (top ?d ?from))
      (top ?d ?to)
      (not (empty ?to))
      (empty ?from)
    )
  )

  ;; Move when destination is empty and moved disk has a disk immediately below it
  (:action move-by-mover-empty-with-below
    :parameters (?s1 - step ?s2 - step ?d - disk ?l - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (current-step ?s1)
      (next ?s1 ?s2)
      (required-move ?s1 ?d ?from ?to)
      (top ?d ?from)
      (empty ?to)
      (immed-below ?d ?l)
      (has-below ?d)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (current-step ?s1))
      (current-step ?s2)

      ;; move disk between pegs
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)

      ;; source updates: disk below becomes new top
      (not (immed-below ?d ?l))
      (top ?l ?from)

      (not (top ?d ?from))
      (top ?d ?to)

      ;; emptiness updates
      (not (empty ?to))
      (not (empty ?from))

      ;; moved disk will no longer have a below disk (destination empty)
      (not (has-below ?d))
    )
  )

  ;; Move when destination has a top disk e larger than d and moved disk has no disk below it
  (:action move-by-mover-nonempty-no-below
    :parameters (?s1 - step ?s2 - step ?d - disk ?e - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (current-step ?s1)
      (next ?s1 ?s2)
      (required-move ?s1 ?d ?from ?to)
      (top ?d ?from)
      (top ?e ?to)
      (larger ?e ?d)
      (not (has-below ?d))
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (current-step ?s1))
      (current-step ?s2)

      ;; move disk between pegs
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)

      ;; destination updates: old top becomes immediately below moved disk
      (not (top ?e ?to))
      (immed-below ?d ?e)
      (has-below ?d)
      (top ?d ?to)

      ;; source updates: becomes empty (no below)
      (not (top ?d ?from))
      (empty ?from)

      ;; destination was not empty already, so not (empty ?to) ensured by precondition of top ?e ?to
    )
  )

  ;; Move when destination has a top disk e larger than d and moved disk has an immediate below l
  (:action move-by-mover-nonempty-with-below
    :parameters (?s1 - step ?s2 - step ?d - disk ?l - disk ?e - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
      (current-step ?s1)
      (next ?s1 ?s2)
      (required-move ?s1 ?d ?from ?to)
      (top ?d ?from)
      (immed-below ?d ?l)
      (has-below ?d)
      (top ?e ?to)
      (larger ?e ?d)
    )
    :effect (and
      (not (current-step ?s1))
      (current-step ?s2)

      ;; move the disk
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (on ?d ?to)

      ;; remove immediate-below linking to old lower disk; make that lower disk the new top of source
      (not (immed-below ?d ?l))
      (top ?l ?from)

      ;; destination updates: old top becomes below moved disk
      (not (top ?e ?to))
      (immed-below ?d ?e)
      (top ?d ?to)

      ;; moved disk still has a below disk at the destination (has-below remains true)
      (has-below ?d)

      ;; source is not empty after move because lower disk l becomes top
      (not (empty ?from))

      ;; ensure the moved-from top predicate removed
      (not (top ?d ?from))
    )
  )
)
================================================================================


PROBLEM
------------------------------
(define (problem hanoi-7-left-to-middle)
  (:domain hanoi-multiagent)

  (:objects
    a b c d e f g - disk
    left middle right - peg
    ;; steps: step1..step128 (we need one extra to be the successor of step127)
    step1 step2 step3 step4 step5 step6 step7 step8 step9 step10
    step11 step12 step13 step14 step15 step16 step17 step18 step19 step20
    step21 step22 step23 step24 step25 step26 step27 step28 step29 step30
    step31 step32 step33 step34 step35 step36 step37 step38 step39 step40
    step41 step42 step43 step44 step45 step46 step47 step48 step49 step50
    step51 step52 step53 step54 step55 step56 step57 step58 step59 step60
    step61 step62 step63 step64 step65 step66 step67 step68 step69 step70
    step71 step72 step73 step74 step75 step76 step77 step78 step79 step80
    step81 step82 step83 step84 step85 step86 step87 step88 step89 step90
    step91 step92 step93 step94 step95 step96 step97 step98 step99 step100
    step101 step102 step103 step104 step105 step106 step107 step108 step109 step110
    step111 step112 step113 step114 step115 step116 step117 step118 step119 step120
    step121 step122 step123 step124 step125 step126 step127 step128 - step
  )

  (:init
    ;; current step starts at step1
    (current-step step1)

    ;; successor links
    (next step1 step2) (next step2 step3) (next step3 step4) (next step4 step5)
    (next step5 step6) (next step6 step7) (next step7 step8) (next step8 step9)
    (next step9 step10) (next step10 step11) (next step11 step12) (next step12 step13)
    (next step13 step14) (next step14 step15) (next step15 step16) (next step16 step17)
    (next step17 step18) (next step18 step19) (next step19 step20) (next step20 step21)

    (next step85 step86) (next step86 step87) (next step87 step88) (next step88 step89)
    (next step89 step90) (next step90 step91) (next step91 step92) (next step92 step93)
    (next step93 step94) (next step94 step95) (next step95 step96) (next step96 step97)
    (next step97 step98) (next step98 step99) (next step99 step100) (next step100 step101)

  (:goal (and
    ;; all disks must be on middle
    (on a middle) (on b middle) (on c middle) (on d middle) (on e middle) (on f middle) (on g middle)

    ;; exact stack ordering top-to-bottom: a b c d e f g
    (top a middle)
    (immed-below a b) (immed-below b c) (immed-below c d)
    (immed-below d e) (immed-below e f) (immed-below f g)

    ;; other pegs empty
    (empty left) (empty right)
  ))
)

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg step)\n\n  (:predicates\n    ;; disk placement on pegs\n    (on ?d - disk ?p - peg)\n    ;; immediate adjacency: ?upper is directly above ?lower on same peg\n    (immed-below ?upper - disk ?lower - disk)\n    ;; disk has any disk below it (at least one)\n    (has-below ?d - disk)\n    ;; disk is the top disk of a peg\n    (top ?d - disk ?p - peg)\n    ;; peg is empty (no disks)\n    (empty ?p - peg)\n\n    ;; explicit discrete time progression\n    (current-step ?s - step)\n    (next ?s1 - step ?s2 - step)\n\n    ;; require a specific disk move at a given step: hard ordering constraint\n    (required-move ?s - step ?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg)\n\n    ;; size order predicate: larger ?x ?y means x is strictly larger than y\n    (larger ?x - disk ?y - disk)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from ?from to an empty destination ?to,\n  ;; when the moved disk has no disk immediately below it at the source.\n  (:action move-empty-no-below\n    :parameters (?s1 - step ?s2 - step ?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg)\n    :precondition (and\n      (current-step ?s1)\n      (next ?s1 ?s2)\n      (required-move ?s1 ?d ?from ?to)\n      (top ?d ?from)\n      (empty ?to)\n      (not (has-below ?d))\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; advance time\n      (not (current-step ?s1))\n      (current-step ?s2)\n\n      ;; move disk placement\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (on ?d ?to)\n\n      ;; source updates: disk removed was top, source becomes empty\n      (not (top ?d ?from))\n      (empty ?from)\n\n      ;; destination updates: disk becomes top and destination no longer empty\n      (top ?d ?to)\n      (not (empty ?to))\n\n      ;; moved disk continues to have no disk below\n      (not (has-below ?d))\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; PROBLEM
------------------------------
I am practicing the Tower of Hanoi puzzle. Here is the action I can do

Move the top disk from one peg to another peg

I must obey the following rules:
I can move only one disk at a time.
I may only move a disk that is on top of a peg.
I can never place a larger disk on top of a smaller disk.
Once a disk is moved, it keeps its relative size ordering with the others.

[STATEMENT]
There are 7 disks in total. From smallest to largest they are disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G.
As initial conditions I have that, the middle peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, while the right peg and the left peg are empty.
My goal is to have that the left peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, and both the middle peg and the right peg are empty again.
The right peg can be used as an intermediate parking spot but must end up empty.

My plan is as follows:

ENVIRONMENT
------------------------------
I am practicing the Tower of Hanoi puzzle. Here is the action I can do

Move the top disk from one peg to another peg

I must obey the following rules:
I can move only one disk at a time.
I may only move a disk that is on top of a peg.
I can never place a larger disk on top of a smaller disk.
Once a disk is moved, it keeps its relative size ordering with the others.

[STATEMENT]
There are 7 disks in total. From smallest to largest they are disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G.
As initial conditions I have that, the middle peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, while the right peg and the left peg are empty.
My goal is to have that the left peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, and both the middle peg and the right peg are empty again.
The right peg can be used as an intermediate parking spot but must end up empty.

My plan is as follows:

FINAL-PLAN
------------------------------
<domain>
(define (domain hanoi-7)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types disk peg - place)

  (:predicates
    ;; disk is directly on place (a disk or a peg)
    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)
    ;; disk has no disk on top of it (is top of its local stack)
    (clear ?d - disk)
    ;; peg has no disk directly on it (is empty)
    (empty ?p - peg)
    ;; static size ordering: first disk is smaller than second
    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)
  )

  ;; Move a clear disk that is directly on a disk, onto another clear disk.
  (:action move-from-disk-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - disk ?to - disk)
    :precondition (and
                    (on ?d ?from)
                    (clear ?d)
                    (clear ?to)
                    (smaller ?d ?to)
                    (not (on ?d ?to))
                  )
    :effect (and
              (not (on ?d ?from))
              (on ?d ?to)
              ;; the disk we removed from becomes clear (no disk on it)
              (clear ?from)
              ;; the disk we placed onto is no longer clear
              (not (clear ?to))
            )
  )

  ;; Move a clear disk that is directly on a disk, onto an empty peg.
  (:action move-from-disk-to-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - disk ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
                    (on ?d ?from)
                    (clear ?d)
                    (empty ?to)
                    (not (on ?d ?to))
                  )
    :effect (and
              (not (on ?d ?from))
              (on ?d ?to)
              ;; the disk we removed from becomes clear
              (clear ?from)
              ;; the peg we placed onto is no longer empty
              (not (empty ?to))
            )
  )

  ;; Move a clear disk that is directly on a peg, onto a clear disk.
  ;; (A disk directly on a peg and clear implies it is the only disk directly on that peg;
  ;; after removal the peg becomes empty.)
  (:action move-from-peg-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - disk)
    :precondition (and
                    (on ?d ?from)
                    (clear ?d)
                    (clear ?to)
                    (smaller ?d ?to)
                    (not (on ?d ?to))
                  )
    :effect (and
              (not (on ?d ?from))
              (on ?d ?to)
              ;; the peg we removed from becomes empty
              (empty ?from)
              ;; the disk we placed onto is no longer clear
              (not (clear ?to))
            )
  )

  ;; Move a clear disk that is directly on a peg, onto an empty peg.
  (:action move-from-peg-to-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
                    (on ?d ?from)
                    (clear ?d)
                    (empty ?to)
                    (not (on ?d ?to))
                  )
    :effect (and
              (not (on ?d ?from))
              (on ?d ?to)
              ;; source peg becomes empty, destination peg no longer empty
              (empty ?from)
              (not (empty ?to))
            )
  )

)
</domain>

<problem>
(define (problem hanoi-7-problem)
  (:domain hanoi-7)
  (:objects
    A B C D E F G - disk
    left middle right - peg
  )

  (:init
    ;; initial stack on middle: G on middle (bottom), then F on G, E on F, ..., A on B (top)
    (on G middle)
    (on F G)
    (on E F)
    (on D E)
    (on C D)
    (on B C)
    (on A B)

    ;; top-most disk is A
    (clear A)

    ;; pegs left and right are initially empty; middle is not empty (no empty fact)
    (empty left)
    (empty right)

    ;; size ordering: A smallest, G largest. Enumerate all smaller relations.
    ;; A smaller than B,C,D,E,F,G
    (smaller A B) (smaller A C) (smaller A D) (smaller A E) (smaller A F) (smaller A G)
    ;; B smaller than C,D,E,F,G
    (smaller B C) (smaller B D) (smaller B E) (smaller B F) (smaller B G)
    ;; C smaller than D,E,F,G
    (smaller C D) (smaller C E) (smaller C F) (smaller C G)
    ;; D smaller than E,F,G
    (smaller D E) (smaller D F) (smaller D G)
    ;; E smaller than F,G
    (smaller E F) (smaller E G)
    ;; F smaller than G
    (smaller F G)
  )

  (:goal (and
    ;; final stack on left: G on left (bottom), then F on G, ..., A on B (top)
    (on G left)
    (on F G)
    (on E F)
    (on D E)
    (on C D)
    (on B C)
    (on A B)

    ;; other pegs must be empty
    (empty middle)
    (empty right)
  ))
)
</problem>
================================================================================


DOMAIN
------------------------------
(define (domain hanoi-7)
  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)
  (:types disk peg - place)

  (:predicates
    ;; disk is directly on place (a disk or a peg)
    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)
    ;; disk has no disk on top of it (is top of its local stack)
    (clear ?d - disk)
    ;; peg has no disk directly on it (is empty)
    (empty ?p - peg)
    ;; static size ordering: first disk is smaller than second
    (smaller ?d1 - disk ?d2 - disk)
  )

  ;; Move a clear disk that is directly on a disk, onto another clear disk.
  (:action move-from-disk-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - disk ?to - disk)
    :precondition (and
                    (on ?d ?from)
                    (clear ?d)
                    (clear ?to)
                    (smaller ?d ?to)
                    (not (on ?d ?to))
                  )
    :effect (and
              (not (on ?d ?from))
              (on ?d ?to)
              ;; the disk we removed from becomes clear (no disk on it)
              (clear ?from)
              ;; the disk we placed onto is no longer clear
              (not (clear ?to))
            )
  )

  ;; Move a clear disk that is directly on a disk, onto an empty peg.
  (:action move-from-disk-to-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - disk ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
                    (on ?d ?from)
                    (clear ?d)
                    (empty ?to)
                    (not (on ?d ?to))
                  )
    :effect (and
              (not (on ?d ?from))
              (on ?d ?to)
              ;; the disk we removed from becomes clear
              (clear ?from)
              ;; the peg we placed onto is no longer empty
              (not (empty ?to))
            )
  )

  ;; Move a clear disk that is directly on a peg, onto a clear disk.
  ;; (A disk directly on a peg and clear implies it is the only disk directly on that peg;
  ;; after removal the peg becomes empty.)
  (:action move-from-peg-to-disk
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - disk)
    :precondition (and
                    (on ?d ?from)
                    (clear ?d)
                    (clear ?to)
                    (smaller ?d ?to)
                    (not (on ?d ?to))
                  )
    :effect (and
              (not (on ?d ?from))
              (on ?d ?to)
              ;; the peg we removed from becomes empty
              (empty ?from)
              ;; the disk we placed onto is no longer clear
              (not (clear ?to))
            )
  )

  ;; Move a clear disk that is directly on a peg, onto an empty peg.
  (:action move-from-peg-to-peg
    :parameters (?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and
                    (on ?d ?from)
                    (clear ?d)
                    (empty ?to)
                    (not (on ?d ?to))
                  )
    :effect (and
              (not (on ?d ?from))
              (on ?d ?to)
              ;; source peg becomes empty, destination peg no longer empty
              (empty ?from)
              (not (empty ?to))
            )
  )

)
================================================================================


PROBLEM
------------------------------
(define (problem hanoi-7-problem)
  (:domain hanoi-7)
  (:objects
    A B C D E F G - disk
    left middle right - peg
  )

  (:init
    ;; initial stack on middle: G on middle (bottom), then F on G, E on F, ..., A on B (top)
    (on G middle)
    (on F G)
    (on E F)
    (on D E)
    (on C D)
    (on B C)
    (on A B)

    ;; top-most disk is A
    (clear A)

    ;; pegs left and right are initially empty; middle is not empty (no empty fact)
    (empty left)
    (empty right)

    ;; size ordering: A smallest, G largest. Enumerate all smaller relations.
    ;; A smaller than B,C,D,E,F,G
    (smaller A B) (smaller A C) (smaller A D) (smaller A E) (smaller A F) (smaller A G)
    ;; B smaller than C,D,E,F,G
    (smaller B C) (smaller B D) (smaller B E) (smaller B F) (smaller B G)
    ;; C smaller than D,E,F,G
    (smaller C D) (smaller C E) (smaller C F) (smaller C G)
    ;; D smaller than E,F,G
    (smaller D E) (smaller D F) (smaller D G)
    ;; E smaller than F,G
    (smaller E F) (smaller E G)
    ;; F smaller than G
    (smaller F G)
  )

  (:goal (and
    ;; final stack on left: G on left (bottom), then F on G, ..., A on B (top)
    (on G left)
    (on F G)
    (on E F)
    (on D E)
    (on C D)
    (on B C)
    (on A B)

    ;; other pegs must be empty
    (empty middle)
    (empty right)
  ))
)
================================================================================

125. Step 125 (s124  s125): Move disk A from on disk B to peg middle.
126. Step 126 (s125  s126): Move disk B from peg right to on disk C.
127. Step 127 (s126  s127): Move disk A from peg middle to on disk B.

This sequence exactly follows the provided plan (127 unit-cost moves, s0  s127) and results in the full stack AG transferred from the middle peg to the left peg in proper order, leaving middle and right empty.
================================================================================


PROBLEM
------------------------------
I am practicing the Tower of Hanoi puzzle. Here is the action I can do

Move the top disk from one peg to another peg

I must obey the following rules:
I can move only one disk at a time.
I may only move a disk that is on top of a peg.
I can never place a larger disk on top of a smaller disk.
Once a disk is moved, it keeps its relative size ordering with the others.

[STATEMENT]
There are 7 disks in total. From smallest to largest they are disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G.
As initial conditions I have that, the right peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, while the middle peg and the left peg are empty.
My goal is to have that the left peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, and both the right peg and the middle peg are empty again.
The middle peg can be used as an intermediate parking spot but must end up empty.

My plan is as follows:

[PLAN]
================================================================================


ENVIRONMENT
------------------------------
I am practicing the Tower of Hanoi puzzle. Here is the action I can do

Move the top disk from one peg to another peg

I must obey the following rules:
I can move only one disk at a time.
I may only move a disk that is on top of a peg.
I can never place a larger disk on top of a smaller disk.
Once a disk is moved, it keeps its relative size ordering with the others.

[STATEMENT]
There are 7 disks in total. From smallest to largest they are disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G.
As initial conditions I have that, the right peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, while the middle peg and the left peg are empty.
My goal is to have that the left peg holds, from top to bottom, disk A, disk B, disk C, disk D, disk E, disk F, and disk G, and both the right peg and the middle peg are empty again.
The middle peg can be used as an intermediate parking spot but must end up empty.

My plan is as follows:

[PLAN]
================================================================================


FINAL-PLAN
------------------------------
<domain>
(define (domain hanoi_multiagent)
  (:requirements :typing :strips :negative-preconditions)
  (:types disk peg - place step)
  (:predicates
    ;; spatial / stack state
    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)        ; disk d is directly on place p (peg or disk)
    (clear ?p - place)               ; place p has nothing directly on it (is top)
    (holding ?d - disk)              ; mover is holding disk d
    ;; step control and sequencing
    (enabled ?s - step)              ; step is enabled (next to execute)
    (locked-step ?s - step)          ; locks for step are acquired
    (placed ?s - step)               ; the step has completed the place action
    (asserted-top ?s - step)         ; verifier asserted the top disk precondition for step
    (transported ?s - step)          ; transport phase completed for step
    (check-passed ?s - step)         ; auditor validated the placement for step
    ;; step metadata
    (step-from ?s - step ?p - peg)   ; source peg for step
    (step-to ?s - step ?p - peg)     ; target peg for step
    (step-next ?s1 - step ?s2 - step)
    ;; size relation (static)
    (larger ?x - disk ?y - disk)
  )

  ;; ---------------------------
  ;; Actions (multi-agent annotated)
  ;; ---------------------------

  ;; MOVER: acquire locks for the step
  (:action mover_lock
    :parameters (?s - step)
    :precondition (and (enabled ?s))
    :effect (and (locked-step ?s) (not (enabled ?s)))
  )

  ;; VERIFIER: assert that the disk to be picked is the top disk on source
  (:action verifier_assert_top
    :parameters (?s - step ?d - disk ?from - peg)
    :precondition (and (locked-step ?s) (step-from ?s ?from) (on ?d ?from) (clear ?d))
    :effect (and (asserted-top ?s))
  )

  ;; MOVER: pick the top disk from source
  (:action mover_pick
    :parameters (?s - step ?d - disk ?from - place)
    :precondition (and (locked-step ?s) (asserted-top ?s) (on ?d ?from) (clear ?d))
    :effect (and
      (holding ?d)
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (clear ?from)
      (not (clear ?d))
      (not (asserted-top ?s))
    )
  )

  ;; MOVER: transport (no structural state change, but enforces ordering)
  (:action mover_transport
    :parameters (?s - step ?d - disk)
    :precondition (and (locked-step ?s) (holding ?d))
    :effect (and (transported ?s))
  )

  ;; AUDITOR: validate placing on an empty target peg
  (:action auditor_check_place_empty
    :parameters (?s - step ?d - disk ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and (locked-step ?s) (transported ?s) (step-to ?s ?to) (clear ?to))
    :effect (and (check-passed ?s))
  )

  ;; AUDITOR: validate placing on a disk currently top-of-target
  (:action auditor_check_place_on
    :parameters (?s - step ?d - disk ?below - disk ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and (locked-step ?s) (transported ?s) (step-to ?s ?to) (on ?below ?to) (clear ?below) (larger ?below ?d))
    :effect (and (check-passed ?s))
  )

  ;; MOVER: place onto an empty peg
  (:action mover_place_on_empty
    :parameters (?s - step ?d - disk ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and (locked-step ?s) (holding ?d) (step-to ?s ?to) (check-passed ?s))
    :effect (and
      (on ?d ?to)
      (not (holding ?d))
      (not (clear ?to))
      (clear ?d)
      (placed ?s)
      (not (transported ?s))
      (not (check-passed ?s))
    )
  )

  ;; MOVER: place onto an existing top disk on a peg
  (:action mover_place_on_disk
    :parameters (?s - step ?d - disk ?below - disk ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and (locked-step ?s) (holding ?d) (step-to ?s ?to) (on ?below ?to) (clear ?below) (larger ?below ?d) (check-passed ?s))
    :effect (and
      (on ?d ?below)
      (not (holding ?d))
      (not (clear ?below))
      (clear ?d)
      (placed ?s)
      (not (transported ?s))
      (not (check-passed ?s))
    )
  )

  ;; AUDITOR: release locks and enable next step
  (:action auditor_unlock
    :parameters (?s - step ?next - step)
    :precondition (and (locked-step ?s) (placed ?s) (step-next ?s ?next))
    :effect (and (not (locked-step ?s)) (not (placed ?s)) (enabled ?next))
  )

  ;; Special final unlock (no next step) to release locks at the last step
  (:action auditor_unlock_final
    :parameters (?s - step)
    :precondition (and (locked-step ?s) (placed ?s) (not (step-next ?s ?s)))
    :effect (and (not (locked-step ?s)) (not (placed ?s)))
  )
)
</domain>
</domain>

<problem>
(define (problem hanoi7-instance)
  (:domain hanoi_multiagent)
  (:objects
    A B C D E F G - disk
    left middle right - peg
    ;; steps
    step1 step2 step3 step4 step5 step6 step7 step8 step9 step10
    step11 step12 step13 step14 step15 step16 step17 step18 step19 step20
    step21 step22 step23 step24 step25 step26 step27 step28 step29 step30

    step91 step92 step93 step94 step95 step96 step97 step98 step99 step100

    step111 step112 step113 step114 step115 step116 step117 step118 step119 step120
    step121 step122 step123 step124 step125 step126 step127 - step
  )

  (:init
    ;; initial stack on right peg: G bottom ... A top
    (on G right)
    (on F G)
    (on E F)
    (on D E)
    (on C D)
    (on B C)
    (on A B)

    ;; clear facts: top disk and empty pegs
    (clear A)
    (clear left)
    (clear middle)

    (enabled step1)

    (step-next step85 step86) (step-next step86 step87) (step-next step87 step88) (step-next step88 step89)
    (step-next step89 step90) (step-next step90 step91) (step-next step91 step92) (step-next step92 step93)
    (step-next step93 step94) (step-next step94 step95) (step-next step95 step96) (step-next step96 step97)
    (step-next step97 step98) (step-next step98 step99) (step-next step99 step100) (step-next step100 step101)
    (step-next step101 step102) (step-next step102 step103) (step-next step103 step104) (step-next step104 step105)
    (step-next step105 step106) (step-next step106 step107) (step-next step107 step108) (step-next step108 step109)
    (step-next step109 step110) (step-next step110 step111) (step-next step111 step112) (step-next step112 step113)
    (step-next step113 step114) (step-next step114 step115) (step-next step115 step116) (step-next step116 step117)
    (step-next step117 step118) (step-next step118 step119) (step-next step119 step120) (step-next step120 step121)
    (step-next step121 step122) (step-next step122 step123) (step-next step123 step124) (step-next step124 step125)
    (step-next step125 step126) (step-next step126 step127)

    ;; size relations (larger) -- complete ordering relations
    ;; G larger than F,E,D,C,B,A
    (larger G F) (larger G E) (larger G D) (larger G C) (larger G B) (larger G A)
    ;; F larger than E,D,C,B,A
    (larger F E) (larger F D) (larger F C) (larger F B) (larger F A)
    ;; E larger than D,C,B,A
    (larger E D) (larger E C) (larger E B) (larger E A)
    ;; D larger than C,B,A
    (larger D C) (larger D B) (larger D A)
    ;; C larger than B,A
    (larger C B) (larger C A)
    ;; B larger than A
    (larger B A)
  )

  (:goal
    (and
      ;; final stack on left: G bottom then F,E,D,C,B,A above
      (on G left)
      (on F G)
      (on E F)
      (on D E)
      (on C D)
      (on B C)
      (on A B)
      ;; ensure middle and right pegs are empty (implicitly satisfied if all disks on left,
      ;; but make it explicit by requiring no disk directly on those pegs)
      ;; We assert that no disk is directly on middle or right by enumerating negatives:
      (not (on A middle)) (not (on B middle)) (not (on C middle)) (not (on D middle)) (not (on E middle)) (not (on F middle)) (not (on G middle))
      (not (on A right))  (not (on B right))  (not (on C right))  (not (on D right))  (not (on E right))  (not (on F right))  (not (on G right))
      ;; optionally ensure left is not clear (because stack occupies it), and top A is clear
      (clear A)
    )
  )
)
</problem>
================================================================================


DOMAIN
------------------------------
(define (domain hanoi_multiagent)
  (:requirements :typing :strips :negative-preconditions)
  (:types disk peg - place step)
  (:predicates
    ;; spatial / stack state
    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)        ; disk d is directly on place p (peg or disk)
    (clear ?p - place)               ; place p has nothing directly on it (is top)
    (holding ?d - disk)              ; mover is holding disk d
    ;; step control and sequencing
    (enabled ?s - step)              ; step is enabled (next to execute)
    (locked-step ?s - step)          ; locks for step are acquired
    (placed ?s - step)               ; the step has completed the place action
    (asserted-top ?s - step)         ; verifier asserted the top disk precondition for step
    (transported ?s - step)          ; transport phase completed for step
    (check-passed ?s - step)         ; auditor validated the placement for step
    ;; step metadata
    (step-from ?s - step ?p - peg)   ; source peg for step
    (step-to ?s - step ?p - peg)     ; target peg for step
    (step-next ?s1 - step ?s2 - step)
    ;; size relation (static)
    (larger ?x - disk ?y - disk)
  )

  ;; ---------------------------
  ;; Actions (multi-agent annotated)
  ;; ---------------------------

  ;; MOVER: acquire locks for the step
  (:action mover_lock
    :parameters (?s - step)
    :precondition (and (enabled ?s))
    :effect (and (locked-step ?s) (not (enabled ?s)))
  )

  ;; VERIFIER: assert that the disk to be picked is the top disk on source
  (:action verifier_assert_top
    :parameters (?s - step ?d - disk ?from - peg)
    :precondition (and (locked-step ?s) (step-from ?s ?from) (on ?d ?from) (clear ?d))
    :effect (and (asserted-top ?s))
  )

  ;; MOVER: pick the top disk from source
  (:action mover_pick
    :parameters (?s - step ?d - disk ?from - place)
    :precondition (and (locked-step ?s) (asserted-top ?s) (on ?d ?from) (clear ?d))
    :effect (and
      (holding ?d)
      (not (on ?d ?from))
      (clear ?from)
      (not (clear ?d))
      (not (asserted-top ?s))
    )
  )

  ;; MOVER: transport (no structural state change, but enforces ordering)
  (:action mover_transport
    :parameters (?s - step ?d - disk)
    :precondition (and (locked-step ?s) (holding ?d))
    :effect (and (transported ?s))
  )

  ;; AUDITOR: validate placing on an empty target peg
  (:action auditor_check_place_empty
    :parameters (?s - step ?d - disk ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and (locked-step ?s) (transported ?s) (step-to ?s ?to) (clear ?to))
    :effect (and (check-passed ?s))
  )

  ;; AUDITOR: validate placing on a disk currently top-of-target
  (:action auditor_check_place_on
    :parameters (?s - step ?d - disk ?below - disk ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and (locked-step ?s) (transported ?s) (step-to ?s ?to) (on ?below ?to) (clear ?below) (larger ?below ?d))
    :effect (and (check-passed ?s))
  )

  ;; MOVER: place onto an empty peg
  (:action mover_place_on_empty
    :parameters (?s - step ?d - disk ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and (locked-step ?s) (holding ?d) (step-to ?s ?to) (check-passed ?s))
    :effect (and
      (on ?d ?to)
      (not (holding ?d))
      (not (clear ?to))
      (clear ?d)
      (placed ?s)
      (not (transported ?s))
      (not (check-passed ?s))
    )
  )

  ;; MOVER: place onto an existing top disk on a peg
  (:action mover_place_on_disk
    :parameters (?s - step ?d - disk ?below - disk ?to - peg)
    :precondition (and (locked-step ?s) (holding ?d) (step-to ?s ?to) (on ?below ?to) (clear ?below) (larger ?below ?d) (check-passed ?s))
    :effect (and
      (on ?d ?below)
      (not (holding ?d))
      (not (clear ?below))
      (clear ?d)
      (placed ?s)
      (not (transported ?s))
      (not (check-passed ?s))
    )
  )

  ;; AUDITOR: release locks and enable next step
  (:action auditor_unlock
    :parameters (?s - step ?next - step)
    :precondition (and (locked-step ?s) (placed ?s) (step-next ?s ?next))
    :effect (and (not (locked-step ?s)) (not (placed ?s)) (enabled ?next))
  )

  ;; Special final unlock (no next step) to release locks at the last step
  (:action auditor_unlock_final
    :parameters (?s - step)
    :precondition (and (locked-step ?s) (placed ?s) (not (step-next ?s ?s)))
    :effect (and (not (locked-step ?s)) (not (placed ?s)))
  )
)
================================================================================


PROBLEM
------------------------------

    A B C D E F G - disk
    left middle right - peg
    ;; steps

    (step-next step125 step126) (step-next step126 step127)

    ;; size relations (larger) -- complete ordering relations
    ;; G larger than F,E,D,C,B,A
    (larger G F) (larger G E) (larger G D) (larger G C) (larger G B) (larger G A)
    ;; F larger than E,D,C,B,A
    (larger F E) (larger F D) (larger F C) (larger F B) (larger F A)
    ;; E larger than D,C,B,A
    (larger E D) (larger E C) (larger E B) (larger E A)
    ;; D larger than C,B,A
    (larger D C) (larger D B) (larger D A)
    ;; C larger than B,A
    (larger C B) (larger C A)
    ;; B larger than A
    (larger B A)
  )

  (:goal
    (and
      ;; final stack on left: G bottom then F,E,D,C,B,A above
      (on G left)
      (on F G)
      (on E F)
      (on D E)
      (on C D)
      (on B C)
      (on A B)
      ;; ensure middle and right pegs are empty (implicitly satisfied if all disks on left,
      ;; but make it explicit by requiring no disk directly on those pegs)
      ;; We assert that no disk is directly on middle or right by enumerating negatives:
      (not (on A middle)) (not (on B middle)) (not (on C middle)) (not (on D middle)) (not (on E middle)) (not (on F middle)) (not (on G middle))
      (not (on A right))  (not (on B right))  (not (on C right))  (not (on D right))  (not (on E right))  (not (on F right))  (not (on G right))
      ;; optionally ensure left is not clear (because stack occupies it), and top A is clear
      (clear A)
    )
  )
)

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi_multiagent)\n  (:requirements :typing :strips :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg - place step)\n  (:predicates\n    ;; spatial / stack state\n    (on ?d - disk ?p - place)        ; disk d is directly on place p (peg or disk)\n    (clear ?p - place)               ; place p has nothing directly on it (is top)\n    (holding ?d - disk)              ; mover is holding disk d\n    ;; step control and sequencing\n    (enabled ?s - step)              ; step is enabled (next to execute)\n    (locked-step ?s - step)          ; locks for step are acquired\n    (placed ?s - step)               ; the step has completed the place action\n    (asserted-top ?s - step)         ; verifier asserted the top disk precondition for step\n    (transported ?s - step)          ; transport phase completed for step\n    (check-passed ?s - step)         ; auditor validated the placement for step\n    ;; step metadata\n    (step-from ?s - step ?p - peg)   ; source peg for step\n    (step-to ?s - step ?p - peg)     ; target peg for step\n    (step-next ?s1 - step ?s2 - step)\n    ;; size relation (static)\n    (larger ?x - disk ?y - disk)\n  )\n\n  ;; ---------------------------\n  ;; Actions (multi-agent annotated)\n  ;; ---------------------------\n\n  ;; MOVER: acquire locks for the step\n  (:action mover_lock\n    :parameters (?s - step)\n    :precondition (and (enabled ?s))\n    :effect (and (locked-step ?s) (not (enabled ?s)))\n  )\n\n  ;; VERIFIER: assert that the disk to be picked is the top disk on source\n  (:action verifier_assert_top\n    :parameters (?s - step ?d - disk ?from - peg)\n    :precondition (and (locked-step ?s) (step-from ?s ?from) (on ?d ?from) (clear ?d))\n    :effect (and (asserted-top ?s))\n  )\n\n  ;; MOVER: pick the top disk from source\n  (:action mover_pick\n    :parameters (?s - step ?d - disk ?from - place)\n    :precondition (and (locked-step ?s) (asserted-top ?s) (on ?d ?from) (clear ?d))\n    :effect (and\n      (holding ?d)\n      (not (on ?d ?from))\n      (clear ?from)\n      (not (clear ?d))\n      (not (asserted-top ?s))\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; MOVER: transport (no structural state change, but enforces ordering)\n  (:action mover_transport\n    :parameters (?s - step ?d - disk)\n    :precondition (and (locked-step ?s) (holding ?d))\n    :effect (and (transported ?s))\n  )\n\n  ;; AUDITOR: validate placing on an empty target peg\n  (:action auditor_check_place_empty\n    :parameters (?s - step ?d - disk ?to - peg)\n    :precondition (and (locked-step ?s) (transported ?s) (step-to ?s ?to) (clear ?to))\n    :effect (and (check-passed ?s))\n  )\n\n  ;; AUDITOR: validate placing on a disk currently top-of-target\n  (:action auditor_check_place_on\n    :parameters (?s - step ?d - disk ?below - disk ?to - peg)\n    :precondition (and (locked-step ?s) (transported ?s) (step-to ?s ?to) (on ?below ?to) (clear ?below) (larger ?below ?d))\n    :effect (and (check-passed ?s))\n  )\n\n  ;; MOVER: place onto an empty peg\n  (:action mover_place_on_empty\n    :parameters (?s - step ?d - disk ?to - peg)\n    :precondition (and (locked-step ?s) (holding ?d) (step-to ?s ?to) (check-passed ?s))\n    :effect (and\n      (on ?d ?to)\n      (not (holding ?d))\n      (not (clear ?to))\n      (clear ?d)\n      (placed ?s)\n      (not (transported ?s))\n      (not (check-passed ?s))\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; MOVER: place onto an existing top disk on a peg\n  (:action mover_place_on_disk\n    :parameters (?s - step ?d - disk ?below - disk ?to - peg)\n    :precondition (and (locked-step ?s) (holding ?d) (step-to ?s ?to) (on ?below ?to) (clear ?below) (larger ?below ?d) (check-passed ?s))\n    :effect (and\n      (on ?d ?below)\n      (not (holding ?d))\n      (not (clear ?below))\n      (clear ?d)\n      (placed ?s)\n      (not (transported ?s))\n      (not (check-passed ?s))\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; AUDITOR: release locks and enable next step\n  (:action auditor_unlock\n    :parameters (?s - step ?next - step)\n    :precondition (and (locked-step ?s) (placed ?s) (step-next ?s ?next))\n    :effect (and (not (locked-step ?s)) (not (placed ?s)) (enabled ?next))\n  )\n\n  ;; Special final unlock (no next step) to release locks at the last step\n  (:action auditor_unlock_final\n    :parameters (?s - step)\n    :precondition (and (locked-step ?s) (placed ?s) (not (step-next ?s ?s)))\n    :effect (and (not (locked-step ?s)) (not (placed ?s)))\n  )\n)",

successor relation on levels: (succ ?lvl1 ?lvl2) means lvl2 = lvl1 + 1\n    (succ ?lvl1 ?lvl2)\n    ;; sequencing of steps\n    (enabled ?s)\n    (step-next ?s1 ?s2)\n    (last-step ?s)\n    ;; size relation: larger disk than\n    (larger ?x ?y)\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from a source peg to an empty target peg, when this step has a successor.\n  (:action move_to_empty_next\n    :parameters (?s ?d ?from ?to ?lfrom ?lfrom_prev ?lto ?next)\n    :precondition (and\n      (enabled ?s)\n      (at ?d ?from ?lfrom)\n      (succ ?lfrom_prev ?lfrom)         ; ?lfrom_prev is the new height after removing ?d\n      (height ?from ?lfrom)\n      (height ?to lvl0)                 ; target peg currently empty (height lvl0)\n      (succ lvl0 ?lto)                  ; new target height will be ?lto (lvl1)\n      (step-next ?s ?next)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      ;; update disk position\n      (not (at ?d ?from ?lfrom))\n      (at ?d ?to ?lto)\n      ;; update source height: from ?lfrom -> ?lfrom_prev\n      (not (height ?from ?lfrom))\n      (height ?from ?lfrom_prev)\n      ;; update target height: from lvl0 -> ?lto\n      (not (height ?to lvl0))\n      (height ?to ?lto)\n      ;; advance step\n      (not (enabled ?s))\n      (enabled ?next)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move a top disk from a source peg to an empty target peg, when this is the final step.\n  (:action move_to_empty_final\n    :parameters (?s ?d ?from ?to ?lfrom ?lfrom_prev ?lto)\n    :precondition (and\n      (enabled ?s)\n      (at ?d ?from ?lfrom)\n      (succ ?lfrom_prev ?lfrom)\n      (height ?from ?lfrom)\n      (height ?to lvl0)\n      (succ lvl0 ?lto)\n      (last-step ?s)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (at ?d ?from ?lfrom))\n      (at ?d ?to ?lto)\n      (not (height ?from ?lfrom))\n      (height ?from ?lfrom_prev)\n      (not (height ?to lvl0))\n      (height ?to ?lto)\n      (not (enabled ?s))\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;;     "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg level step)\n\n  (:predicates\n    (at ?d - disk ?p - peg ?l - level)       ; disk ?d at peg ?p at level ?l\n    (height ?p - peg ?l - level)             ; current height level of peg ?p is ?l\n    (succ ?l1 - level ?l2 - level)           ; successor relation on levels: ?l2 = ?l1 + 1\n    (enabled ?s - step)                      ; step ?s is enabled / current\n    (step-next ?s1 - step ?s2 - step)        ; ordering of steps\n    (last-step ?s - step)                    ; marks final step\n    (larger ?x - disk ?y - disk)             ; disk ?x is larger than disk ?y\n  )\n\n  ;; Move top disk from a non-empty source peg to an empty target peg, advance to next step.\n  (:action move_to_empty_next\n    :parameters (?s - step ?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg\n                 ?lfrom - level ?lfrom_prev - level ?lto - level ?next - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (enabled ?s)\n      (at ?d ?from ?lfrom)\n      (succ ?lfrom_prev ?lfrom)        ; ?lfrom_prev is the level after removing ?d\n      (height ?from ?lfrom)\n      (height ?to lvl0)                ; target currently empty (lvl0)\n      (succ lvl0 ?lto)                 ; new target height after placing ?d\n      (step-next ?s ?next)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (at ?d ?from ?lfrom))\n      (at ?d ?to ?lto)\n      (not (height ?from ?lfrom))\n      (height ?from ?lfrom_prev)\n      (not (height ?to lvl0))\n      (height ?to ?lto)\n      (not (enabled ?s))\n      (enabled ?next)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move top disk from a non-empty source peg to an empty target peg, final step (no next).\n  (:action move_to_empty_final\n    :parameters (?s - step ?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg\n                 ?lfrom - level ?lfrom_prev - level ?lto - level)\n    :precondition (and\n      (enabled ?s)\n      (at ?d ?from ?lfrom)\n      (succ ?lfrom_prev ?lfrom)\n      (height ?from ?lfrom)\n      (height ?to lvl0)\n      (succ lvl0 ?lto)\n      (last-step ?s)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (at ?d ?from ?lfrom))\n      (at ?d ?to ?lto)\n      (not (height ?from ?lfrom))\n      (height ?from ?lfrom_prev)\n      (not (height ?to lvl0))\n      (height ?to ?lto)\n      (not (enabled ?s))\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move top disk from a non-empty source peg onto a non-empty target peg, advance to next step.\n  (:action move_onto_disk_next\n    :parameters (?s - step ?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg\n                 ?lfrom - level ?lfrom_prev - level ?lto_prev - level ?lto - level\n                 ?below - disk ?next - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (enabled ?s)\n      (at ?d ?from ?lfrom)\n      (succ ?lfrom_prev ?lfrom)\n      (height ?from ?lfrom)\n      (height ?to ?lto_prev)            ; target non-empty, top at ?lto_prev\n      (succ ?lto_prev ?lto)              ; new target level after placing ?d\n      (at ?below ?to ?lto_prev)          ; ?below is current top disk on ?to\n      (larger ?below ?d)                 ; size constraint: below larger than d\n      (step-next ?s ?next)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (at ?d ?from ?lfrom))\n      (at ?d ?to ?lto)\n      (not (height ?from ?lfrom))\n      (height ?from ?lfrom_prev)\n      (not (height ?to ?lto_prev))\n      (height ?to ?lto)\n      (not (enabled ?s))\n      (enabled ?next)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move top disk from a non-empty source peg onto a non-empty target peg, final step.\n  (:action move_onto_disk_final\n    :parameters (?s - step ?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg\n                 ?lfrom - level ?lfrom_prev - level ?lto_prev - level ?lto - level\n                 ?below - disk)\n    :precondition (and\n      (enabled ?s)\n      (at ?d ?from ?lfrom)\n      (succ ?lfrom_prev ?lfrom)\n      (height ?from ?lfrom)\n      (height ?to ?lto_prev)\n      (succ ?lto_prev ?lto)\n      (at ?below ?to ?lto_prev)\n      (larger ?below ?d)\n      (last-step ?s)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (at ?d ?from ?lfrom))\n      (at ?d ?to ?lto)\n      (not (height ?from ?lfrom))\n      (height ?from ?lfrom_prev)\n      (not (height ?to ?lto_prev))\n      (height ?to ?lto)\n      (not (enabled ?s))\n    )\n  )\n)",

    "pddl_domain": "(define (domain hanoi)\n  (:requirements :strips :typing :negative-preconditions)\n  (:types disk peg level step)\n\n  (:predicates\n    (at ?d - disk ?p - peg ?l - level)       ; disk ?d at peg ?p at level ?l (level counts from 0 = empty up)\n    (height ?p - peg ?l - level)             ; current top level (occupied) of peg ?p is ?l\n    (succ ?l1 - level ?l2 - level)           ; successor relation on levels: ?l2 = ?l1 + 1\n    (enabled ?s - step)                      ; step ?s is the currently enabled step\n    (step-next ?s1 - step ?s2 - step)        ; ordering: ?s2 follows ?s1\n    (last-step ?s - step)                    ; marks the final step\n    (larger ?x - disk ?y - disk)             ; disk ?x is larger than disk ?y\n  )\n\n  ;; Move top disk from a non-empty source peg to an empty target peg, advance to next step.\n  (:action move-to-empty-next\n    :parameters (?s - step ?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg\n                 ?lfrom - level ?lfrom_prev - level ?lto - level ?next - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (enabled ?s)\n      (at ?d ?from ?lfrom)\n      (succ ?lfrom_prev ?lfrom)        ; level directly below ?d\n      (height ?from ?lfrom)            ; ?d is top of source peg\n      (height ?to lvl0)                ; target currently empty (the canonical lvl0 object)\n      (succ lvl0 ?lto)                 ; placing will occupy level ?lto\n      (step-next ?s ?next)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (at ?d ?from ?lfrom))\n      (at ?d ?to ?lto)\n      (not (height ?from ?lfrom))\n      (height ?from ?lfrom_prev)\n      (not (height ?to lvl0))\n      (height ?to ?lto)\n      (not (enabled ?s))\n      (enabled ?next)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move top disk from a non-empty source peg to an empty target peg, final step (no next).\n  (:action move-to-empty-final\n    :parameters (?s - step ?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg\n                 ?lfrom - level ?lfrom_prev - level ?lto - level)\n    :precondition (and\n      (enabled ?s)\n      (at ?d ?from ?lfrom)\n      (succ ?lfrom_prev ?lfrom)\n      (height ?from ?lfrom)\n      (height ?to lvl0)\n      (succ lvl0 ?lto)\n      (last-step ?s)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (at ?d ?from ?lfrom))\n      (at ?d ?to ?lto)\n      (not (height ?from ?lfrom))\n      (height ?from ?lfrom_prev)\n      (not (height ?to lvl0))\n      (height ?to ?lto)\n      (not (enabled ?s))\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;; Move top disk from a non-empty source peg onto a non-empty target peg, advance to next step.\n  (:action move-onto-disk-next\n    :parameters (?s - step ?d - disk ?from - peg ?to - peg\n                 ?lfrom - level ?lfrom_prev - level ?lto_prev - level ?lto - level\n                 ?below - disk ?next - step)\n    :precondition (and\n      (enabled ?s)\n      (at ?d ?from ?lfrom)\n      (succ ?lfrom_prev ?lfrom)\n      (height ?from ?lfrom)\n      (height ?to ?lto_prev)            ; target non-empty, top at ?lto_prev\n      (succ ?lto_prev ?lto)              ; new target level after placing ?d\n      (at ?below ?to ?lto_prev)          ; ?below is current top disk on ?to\n      (larger ?below ?d)                 ; size constraint: below larger than d\n      (step-next ?s ?next)\n    )\n    :effect (and\n      (not (at ?d ?from ?lfrom))\n      (at ?d ?to ?lto)\n      (not (height ?from ?lfrom))\n      (height ?from ?lfrom_prev)\n      (not (height ?to ?lto_prev))\n      (height ?to ?lto)\n      (not (enabled ?s))\n      (enabled ?next)\n    )\n  )\n\n  ;;     "pddl_problem": "(define (problem hanoi7)\n  (:domain hanoi)\n  (:objects\n    a b c d e f g - disk\n    left middle right - peg\n    lvl0 lvl1 lvl2 lvl3 lvl4 lvl5 lvl6 lvl7 - level\n    ;; 127
